Fig. 2
). Dorsal shield oval with a waist at level of setae R 1 . Reticulation and sigilla clearly visible. Five pairs of solenostomes are present: gd 2 posteroantiaxial to j 4 , gd 4 posteroantiaxial to s 4 , gd 6 posteroparaxial to s 6 , gd 8 anteroantiaxial to Z 4 and gd 9 paraxial to S 5 . Poroids are not visible on the dorsal shield. Dorsal setae short, most of similar length, and smooth, except S 4 , S 5 , Z 4 and Z 5 which are serrated. Setae Z 5 thicker and capitate (
