Ventral idiosoma (
Fig. 3
). Sternal shield lightly sclerotised and smooth. Posterior margin and poroids pst 1 and pst 2 are not visible. Setae ST 1 , ST 2 and ST 3 inserted on sternal shield. Setae ST 4 tylochorous; poroid pst 3 not visible. Length of sternal shield 96 µm, width 70 µm. Genital sigilla clearly visible. Lateral margin of genital shield with pronounced indentation posterior to ST 5 . Ventrianal shield (VAS) subpentagonal (length 120 µm, width at level of ZV 2 98 µm), slightly constricted at level of JV 3 (width 88 µm). Setae JV 1 , JV 2 , JV 3 and ZV 2 on VAS. Setae ZV 1 , ZV 3 , JV 4 and JV 5 on unsclerotised membrane. Solenostome gv 3 punctiform and posteroparaxial to JV 3 . Setae JV 5 40 ( 30–47 ) long, smooth and slightly spatulate (
