Legs (
Fig. 4
). Leg IV. Four spatulate setae are present on genu: ad 1 18 ( 14–22 ), ad 2 15 ( 12–20 ), pd 1 17 ( 12–20 ), pd 2 18 ( 14–22 ) ( 1-2 / 0-2 / 1 - 1 ). Three capitate setae are present on tibia: ad 1 19 ( 14–24 ), pd 1 20 ( 14–24 ), pd 2 21 ( 16–26 ) ( 1 - 1 / 0-2 / 1 - 1 ). Tarsus: one capitate macroseta pd 33 ( 24–38 ) ( 1 - 1 / 0-1 / 0-1 ).

Chelicerae (
Fig. 6
). Fixed digit with three teeth plus apical tooth. Pilus dentilis evident, long ( 19 µm), with a large base. Movable digit with six teeth in addition to apical tooth.

